'''They Don't Care About Us'''（[[中文|中文]]：'''他们不在乎我们'''）出自[[麥可·傑克森|麥可·傑克森]][[音乐专辑|音乐专辑]]《[[HIStory:_Past,_Present_and_Future,_Book_I|HIStory: Past, Present and Future, Book I]]》。因内容涉嫌歧视犹太人，故该歌曲是傑克森創作單曲之中爭議最多的一首。

此歌曲有两部[[音乐影片|音乐影片]]：'''巴西版'''与'''监狱版'''，两部影片均由[[斯派克·李|斯派克·李]]导演。'''巴西版'''在[[巴西|巴西]]的[[萨尔瓦多_(巴西)|萨尔瓦多]]与[[里约热内卢|里约热内卢]]的[[贫民区|贫民区]]里面拍摄。<ref name="Billboard">{{cite news |url= http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/268216/michael-jackson-remains-a-global-phenomenon |title= Michael Jackson Remains A Global Phenomenon |publisher= Billboard |date= 2009-07-02 |accessdate= 2010-06-10 |archive-date= 2013-04-23 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20130423120818/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/268216/michael-jackson-remains-a-global-phenomenon |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref name="NYT on first TDCAU video">{{cite news |first= Diana Jean |last= Schemo |url= http://www.nytimes.com/1996/02/11/world/rio-frets-as-michael-jackson-plans-to-film-slum.html?pagewanted=all |title= Rio Frets as Michael Jackson Plans to Film Slum |publisher= ''The New York Times'' |date= 1996-02-11 |accessdate= 2010-06-10 |archive-date= 2010-10-04 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20101004135614/http://www.nytimes.com/1996/02/11/world/rio-frets-as-michael-jackson-plans-to-film-slum.html?pagewanted=all |dead-url= no }}</ref>该录影在拍摄之前，巴西国家有关部门曾试图禁止拍摄，因当时巴西正在申办[[2004年奥林匹克运动会|2004年奥林匹克运动会]]，称拍摄会损害国家的形象。但尽管如此，该地区的居民非常高兴可以亲眼见证迈克尔杰克逊的舞步。<ref name="NYT on first TDCAU video" /><ref name=巴西>{{youtube|QNJL6nfu__Q|Michael Jackson - They Don't Care About Us}}</ref>'''监狱版'''引用了多个群体事件录像如[[1992年洛杉磯暴動|1992年洛杉磯暴動]]、[[六四事件|六四事件]]等。<ref name=监狱>{{youtube|97nAvTVeR6o|Michael Jackson - They Don't Care About Us (Official Prison Version)}}</ref>

在1996年至1997年的[[HIStory_World_Tour|HIStory World Tour]]（历史世界巡回演唱会）中，这首歌与同专辑的[[Scream|Scream]]和[[In_The_Closet|In The Closet]]组合在了一起。之后从2009年7月至2010年3月在[[O2體育館|伦敦O2体育场]]的50场[[This_Is_It_(迈克尔·杰克逊演唱会)|This Is It演唱会]]也计划演出，但最终杰克逊在[[美国时间|美国时间]]2009年6月25日去世，导致该演唱会取消。

== 歌曲简介 ==
歌曲开始有儿童高唱“Enough is enough of this garbage!”，在副歌部分更有很多人合唱“All I wanna say is that they don't really care about us!”<ref>"Jackson explains remarks denounced as antisemitism". (June 16, 1995). ''The Boston Globe''.</ref><ref>{{cite web |first= Roger |last= Catlin |url= http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/courant/access/22893883.html?dids=22893883:22893883&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Jun+18%2C+1995&author=ROGER+CATLIN%3B+Courant+Rock+Critic&pub=Hartford+Courant&desc=ONCE+THE+INDISPUTABLE+KING+OF+POP%2C+JACKSON+BADLY+NEEDS+A+HIT+TO+REVIVE+HIS+CAREER+IS+MICHAEL+HISTORY%3F&pqatl=google |title= Once the indisputable King of Pop, Jackson badly needs a hit to revive his career, is Michael HIStory? |publisher= ''The Hartford Courant'' |date= 1995-06-18 |accessdate= 2008-12-13 |archive-date= 2009-06-11 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20090611020735/http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/courant/access/22893883.html?dids=22893883:22893883&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Jun+18%2C+1995&author=ROGER+CATLIN%3B+Courant+Rock+Critic&pub=Hartford+Courant&desc=ONCE+THE+INDISPUTABLE+KING+OF+POP%2C+JACKSON+BADLY+NEEDS+A+HIT+TO+REVIVE+HIS+CAREER+IS+MICHAEL+HISTORY%3F&pqatl=google |dead-url= no }}</ref>这首歌是一首[[流行音乐|流行音乐]]，具有每分钟88次的适度节奏。<ref name="sheetmusic">{{cite web |url= http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0015822 |title= They Don't Care About Us |work= Musicnotes.com |publisher= [[Alfred_Publishing|Alfred Publishing Co]] |accessdate= 2010-04-28 |archive-date= 2016-03-03 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160303184644/http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtd.asp?ppn=MN0015822 |dead-url= no }}</ref>曲子的制作过程使用了[[钢琴|钢琴]]与[[吉他|吉他]]。<ref name="sheetmusic"/>

== 音乐录像 ==

[[File:Saida_do_Olodum_(Carnaval_de_2010).jpg|left]]]][[File:Complexo_do_Alemão.jpg|thumb]] 

第一次拍摄的音乐录像为“巴西版”。[[巴西|巴西]]国家有关机关曾试图禁止杰克逊在[[萨尔瓦多_(巴西)|萨尔瓦多]]与[[里约热内卢|里约热内卢]]拍摄，担心贫困的图像可能会影响旅游业。

该音乐录影中，相当多的居民与围观群众在拍摄期间包围了杰克逊。其中一位妇女在拍摄期间翻过安全线拥抱着与杰克逊一起跳舞，同时另一个女人出现从后面抱住了杰克逊导致杰克逊倒在地上，之后警察将两个女人护送离开，然后导演将杰克逊拉起继续唱歌跳舞。这个事件加入到了音乐视频里面。<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cp-WGDZfGK4 |title= Michael Jackson – They Don't Care About Us HD with subtitle + lyrics Official Music Video |accessdate= 2010-11-17 |format= Youtube video |work= Incident of the two women grabbing Michael Jackson starts at 3:16 in the video, which includes a dance sequence with drumming at the end. Total length: 7:17 |archive-date= 2011-01-06 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20110106222936/http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cp-WGDZfGK4 |dead-url= no }}</ref>在视频的开始，一个巴西女人说：“Michael, eles não ligam pra gente”，意思是“迈克尔，他们不在乎我们”。 

之后杰克逊认为“巴西版”音乐录像没能彻底体现到他的愤怒，于是制作了第二个版本“监狱版”。此录影的拍摄地在监狱，里面包含了杰克逊很多无声的愤怒。影片中更引用了非常多的侵犯人权录像，包括[[羅德尼·金|美国白人警察攻击殴打黑人非裔美国人]]、[[六四事件|六四事件]]、[[三K党|三K党]]与其他包含[[战争罪|战争罪]]、[[种族灭绝罪|种族灭绝罪]]和其他侵犯[[人权|人权]]的[[军事镇压|军事镇压]]的真实画面。<ref>"First look at Michael Jackson's new music video on Entertainment Tonight". (March 29, 1996). [[PR_Newswire|PR Newswire]].</ref>特别地，影片包含[[坦克人|坦克人]]的录像导致“监狱版”音乐录像在中国大陆被禁播，不过在杰克逊于2009年6月25日逝世期间，中国大陆很多视频网站加入了该录像，但约两个星期之后再次被禁播。目前中国大陆的一些网站上有这一音乐录像的删减版。

== 歌词的争议 ==
[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]在1995年6月15日报道该歌曲的歌词包含[[种族主义|种族主义]]和[[反犹太主义|反犹太主义]]的内容，报道强调了涉嫌反犹色彩的歌词“Jew me, sue me, everybody do me/ Kick me, [[kike|kike]] me, don't you black or white me.”<ref name="NYT first raises issue of alleged antisemitism"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.michaeljackson.com/us/music/history-past-present-and-future-book-i/they-dont-care-about-us |title=They Don't Care About Us original lyrics |access-date=2014-07-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304045127/http://www.michaeljackson.com/us/music/history-past-present-and-future-book-i/they-dont-care-about-us |archive-date=2016-03-04 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>杰克逊当时直接回应说明：{{Cquote|<sub>The idea that these lyrics could be deemed objectionable is extremely hurtful to me, and misleading. The song in fact is about the pain of prejudice and hate and is a way to draw attention to social and political problems. I am the voice of the accused and the attacked. I am the voice of everyone. I am the skinhead, I am the Jew, I am the black man, I am the white man. I am not the one who was attacking. It is about the injustices to young people and how the system can wrongfully accuse them. I am angry and outraged that I could be so misinterpreted.</sub><ref name="NYT first raises issue of alleged antisemitism"/>}}

就歌词问题在[[ABC_News|ABC News]]栏目《[[黄金时间|黄金时间]]》接受深度采访时，杰克逊宣称，「那不是反犹太，因为我不是种族主义者 ……...我从来不是一个种族主义者。 我爱所有的种族。」<ref name="NYT first raises issue of alleged antisemitism"/> 歌手同时声称他身边有许多的雇员都是犹太人。同一天，杰克逊得到了来自他的经理与唱片公司的支持，他们用 "brilliant"形容歌词内容，他们反对偏见和断章取义。<ref name="NYT first raises issue of alleged antisemitism">{{cite web|first= Bernard |last= Weinraub |url= http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=990CE4DF113DF936A25755C0A963958260&scp=11&sq=Michael Jackson – HIStory&st=cse |title= In New Lyrics, Jackson Uses Slurs |publisher= ''The New York Times'' |date= 1995-06-15 |accessdate= 2008-12-12}}</ref> 在那之后，两名犹太共同体的领导成员宣称杰克逊尝试写一道批评[[歧视|歧视]]的歌，但实际上却适得其反。他们认为歌词内容并不太适合十几岁的听众，也许他们不了解这首歌的背景，另外这首歌对部分听众来说实在太模棱两可了。他们接受杰克逊的善意，并且建议艺人在专辑的宣传册中写一些说明性的文字。<ref name="June 16, Jewish reaction">{{cite web |url= http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=990CE3D7153EF935A25755C0A963958260 |title= Jewish Response to Jackson |date= 1995-06-16 |publisher= ''The New York Times'' |accessdate= 2008-12-12}}</ref> 

6月17日，杰克逊就他言论发表公开道歉。他承诺将来的专辑拷贝将包含一份道歉信。但是此时已经卖出去了2百万张专辑。歌手得出结论，"我只是希望诸位了解我是多么渴求宽容、 和平与爱， 在此我向可能因此受到伤害的人道歉"。<ref name="June 17- apology, booklet altered">{{cite web|first= Dinitia |last= Smith |url= http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=990CEFD71239F934A25755C0A963958260&scp=19&sq=Michael Jackson – HIStory&st=cse |title= Michael Jackson Apologizes For Hurt Caused by Lyrics |publisher= ''The New York Times'' |date= 1995-06-17 |accessdate= 2008-12-12}}</ref> 之后，在回顾''HIStory''这张专辑的时候， ''纽约时报''的[[乔·恩帕雷利斯|乔·恩帕雷利斯]]声称，“在 ……《They Don't Care About Us》这首歌中，他用爆发的反犹主义对他一整表的兄弟情颂歌撒了谎。”<ref name="HIStory review NYT">{{cite web |first= Jon |last= Pareles |url= http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=990CE0DD123DF93BA25755C0A963958260&scp=4&sq=HIStory+album+michael+jackson+review&st=nyt |title= Pop View; Michael Jackson Is Angry, Understand? |publisher= ''The New York Times'' |date= 1995-06-18 |accessdate= 2008-09-18 |archive-date= 2009-03-11 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20090311005557/http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=990CE0DD123DF93BA25755C0A963958260&scp=4&sq=HIStory+album+michael+jackson+review&st=nyt |dead-url= no }}</ref>

6月21日，《[[西雅图时报|西雅图时报]]》的帕特里克·麦克唐纳批评杰克逊，宣称，"也许他过着优越的生活，但实在是没有理由把这些词语像“Jew me”和“kike”之类的用进一首流行歌曲中，除非你能用一种比较狡猾的方式澄清你是在遣责这些词语"。<ref name="The Seattle Times on HIStory">{{cite web |first= Patrick |last= Macdonald |url= http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=19950621&slug=2127467 |title= 'History' Lesson: Jackson's Living On Past Glories |publisher= ''The Seattle Times'' |date= 1995-06-21 |accessdate= 2008-12-12 |archive-date= 2016-03-03 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20160303195057/http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=19950621&slug=2127467 |dead-url= no }}</ref>

6月23日，杰克逊回到录音室并改变涉嫌反犹太主义的歌词，“Jew me”和“kike me”将用“do me”和“strike me”代替。虽然音乐视频和专辑的一些副本仍然带有原话，但那些原话会被非常响亮的噪音淹没。他重申他接受“这首歌冒犯了一些犹太人”的说法。<ref>{{cite web |first= Chris |last= Riemenschneider |url= http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/21529572.html?dids=21529572:21529572&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Jun+23%2C+1995&author=CHRIS+RIEMENSCHNEIDER&pub=Los+Angeles+Times+(pre-1997+Fulltext)&desc=Jackson+Will+Re-Record+%60Care%27+Lyrics+Pop+music%3A+Michael+Jackson+apologizes+and+says+he+plans+to+change+the+words+in+%60They+Don%27t+Care+About+Us%27+that+some+considered+to+be+racial+slurs.&pqatl=google |title= Jackson Will Re-Record `Care' Lyrics Pop music: Michael Jackson apologizes and says he plans to change the words in `They Don't Care About Us' that some considered to be racial slurs. |publisher= ''Los Angeles Times'' |date= 1995-06-23 |accessdate= 2008-12-12 |archive-date= 2009-06-11 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20090611022141/http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/21529572.html?dids=21529572:21529572&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=Jun+23%2C+1995&author=CHRIS+RIEMENSCHNEIDER&pub=Los+Angeles+Times+(pre-1997+Fulltext)&desc=Jackson+Will+Re-Record+%60Care%27+Lyrics+Pop+music%3A+Michael+Jackson+apologizes+and+says+he+plans+to+change+the+words+in+%60They+Don%27t+Care+About+Us%27+that+some+considered+to+be+racial+slurs.&pqatl=google |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |first=Dinitia |last=Smith |url= http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=990CE1DB1E3AF930A15755C0A963958260 |title= Jackson Plans New Lyrics For Album |publisher= ''The New York Times'' |date= 1995-06-23 |accessdate= 2008-12-12}}</ref>

